With GNU awk:

    echo &quot;010203040F1013&quot; | awk &#39;$1=&quot;0x&quot;$1&#39; FPAT=&#39;..&#39; OFS=&#39;, 0x&#39;
Output:
&lt;pre&gt;
0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x0F, 0x10, 0x13
&lt;/pre&gt;

    $ echo &#39;010203040F1013&#39; | perl -lne &#39;print join &quot;, &quot; , map { &quot;0x$_&quot; } /../g&#39;
    0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x0F, 0x10, 0x13

This one gets every two characters as an array from input line using `/../g` and then uses `map` to convert each matched portion. Finally, the new array is printed by joining the elements with required separator.

    $ echo &#39;010203040F1013&#39; | perl -pe &#39;s/../0x$&amp;, /g; s/, $//&#39;
    0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x0F, 0x10, 0x13
    $ echo &#39;010203040F1013&#39; | sed &#39;s/../0x&amp;, /g; s/, $//&#39;
    0x01, 0x02, 0x03, 0x04, 0x0F, 0x10, 0x13

Here, substitution is used to transform every two characters and then final separator removed using another substitution

